#SerenaWilliams for #Lincoln is a masterclass in artful storytelling in #sporksmarketing, here’s why…👇

Serena Williams’s latest collaboration with Lincoln is nothing short of a poignant masterpiece, seamlessly merging the worlds of sports and heartfelt storytelling. The scene set against the vast expanse of the ocean, featuring Serena and her father, encapsulates not just the strength and resilience of an athlete but the foundational role a parent plays in sculpting that very essence. The waters may be unpredictable, much like the journey of an athlete, but it’s the unwavering trust between Serena and her father, reminiscent of a child’s reliance on their guiding star, that shines through in this beautifully orchestrated campaign.

The artful approach taken here isn’t just about promoting a brand; it’s about paying homage to the deep-rooted relationship between Serena and her father. Their bond is depicted with such grace and subtlety, echoing the countless hours of practice, the sacrifices, and the mutual respect that has made Serena the champion she is today. This campaign taps into the core emotion that many athletes can resonate with—the interplay of trust, guidance, and perseverance, where a parent’s belief becomes the wind beneath an athlete’s wings.

In the realm of marketing, Lincoln’s decision to delve into the intricacies of personal stories holds significant value. By anchoring their brand to authentic, emotionally charged narratives, they transcend beyond the mere promotion of a product. Instead, they offer a window into the souls of icons like Serena, humanizing them and making them relatable. Such storytelling not only strengthens brand association and loyalty but also positions Lincoln as a brand that recognizes and values the profound human experiences behind its ambassadors. This campaign underscores the power of narrative in marketing, proving that stories well-told can become the most potent tool in connecting with audiences.

#serenawilliams #womeninsport #sportsequality

2023 (literally) nearly killed me. 2024 I’m pulling no punches. Here’s to life, here’s to love, here’s to making it through darkness. Here’s to knowing the present version of yourself isn’t the final one, here’s to CHOOSING a new one. Here’s to loss, here’s to family, here’s to leaving the world with a legacy. Support me or deny me, I love you either way. I love this world, I love this life, I love this gift we’ve all been given. 

Here’s to us, here’s to we, here’s to me. 

#HappyNewYear #2024 #Love

F*CK IT story time coming in hot 👇

I started this little project last year where I captured @uhaul products every time I saw one and collected them into fun, punchy videos, in an effort to get the organization’s attention. All this, in a larger effort to get them to donate one of their cargo vans to construct into a 🚚 #QueerSpaceOnWheels 💨 

I stopped the effort bc a group of “community members” had less than savory things to say about it, offering their high-school level criticisms to everyone but myself. This, of course, the antithesis of what we should be standing for or behaving as in the community. 

Thankfully, I’m at a place in my life where I can say…I no longer care. People are entitled to their thoughts and opinions, but they have nothing to do with me. 

So I’m picking this back up. Because I want to, because it brings me joy, it brings OTHERS joy, because even if it doesn’t work out, it’s still fun and joyous and good.

Don’t like it? That’s totally okay and allowed. There’s plenty of folks to talk to about it. 😊

Anyone who has talked to me in the last few years has heard me talk about a “Queer van”. In 2024, we’re just gonna go for it. 

In #2024 I vow to create more silly-ness, do things that yield laughter and encourage people around me to pursue things, and use my own gifts for good things. I’m so excited for what the year will bring! 

#QueerBus #MagicBus #QueerSpace
